BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Indivisible SCI General Meeting March 2026
DTSTART;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T144500
DTEND;TZID=EDT;VALUE=DATE-TIME:20260322T163000
UID:mobilize-910603-5827485@mobilize.us
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://mobilizeamerica.imgix.net/uploads/event/
 march-2026-exodus_20260307134138777670.png
DESCRIPTION:Please arrive by 2:45pm so we can get everyone signed in and s
 tart the meeting promptly at 3:00pm.\n\n### Guest Speaker\nSarah Owen from
  Exodus Refugee Immigration will present a "Refugee 101" training to help 
 us understand the history of refugee resettlement in the U.S. and how we c
 an support those who came to the U.S. to flee persecution.\n\nThe training
  will cover a brief overview of the history of the U.S. Refugee Resettleme
 nt Program\, how the program worked and what it provided (up until recentl
 y)\, and an overview of the role of Exodus and the services that we provid
 e. Sarah will also discuss major 2025 policy changes and the different imm
 igration statuses that are affected by them. \n\n### In-Meeting Action\nSa
 rah will share information about a harmful policy change currently open to
  public comment and how you can submit opposition.\n\n### ISCI Photography
  & Video Policy\nISCI may take photos or videos at meetings and events to 
 document\, share\, and promote our activities. When taking photos or video
 s\, ISCI representatives will do their best to seek explicit consent befor
 e photographing individuals with their faces or names visible. We ask all 
 participants taking personal photos or videos to seek consent as well and 
 respect the wishes of those who do not want to be photographed or recorded
 . **Please note that in public settings\, including protests\, there is al
 ways the possibility of being identifiably photographed.** Ultimately\, th
 e responsibility for protecting our identity lies with each of us individu
 ally. If you are concerned about being photographed or recorded during Ind
 ivisible activities\, we strongly encourage you to cover your face and oth
 er identifiable features.
LOCATION:Monroe County Library - Southwest Branch\, 890 W Gordon Pike\, Bl
 oomington\, IN
URL:https://www.mobilize.us/indivisiblesouthcentralindiana/event/910603/
X-SOURCE:Indivisible SCI
END:VEVENT
